@startuml
skinparam ClassBackgroundColor #b5e8f7
'skinparam linetype polyline
hide circle

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
' Two ways to represent "the pregnancy" in the Pregnancy Status report.
'
'  Option A : the pregnancy is a NEW class -> a Condition.
'             The Condition can be "summarized" into a PregnancyStatus
'             (a ClinicalObservation), which is the IPS-compatible shape.
'
'  Option B : we only ever exchange the "summary" -> the PregnancyStatus
'             Observation (no Condition).
'
'  In BOTH options the detail data (EDD, number of children, end date)
'  are ClinicalObservations.
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

' ── Option B: the new class ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
class "**Pregnancy**\n(Condition)" as PREG #ffe6b5 {
|_ patient 1..1 <<Ref>>
|_ identifier 1..* <<Id>>
|_ author 1..1 <<Ref>>
|_ recordedDate 1..1 <<date>>
|_ clinicalStatus 1..1 <<code>>  (active | resolved)
|_ code 1..1 <<code>>            (pregnant)
|_ onset 0..1 <<date>>
|_ abatement 0..1 <<date>>       (= actualDateOfEndOfPregnancy)
}

' ── The summary / IPS-compatible shape ────────────────────────────────────────
class "**PregnancyStatus**\n(ClinicalObservation)" as PSO {
|_ patient 1..1 <<Ref>>
'|_ pregnancyIdentifier 1..* <<Id>>
|_ recorder 1..1 <<Ref>>
|_ recorded_date 1..1 <<date>>
|_ status 1..1 <<code>>
|_ value : pregnancyStatus 1..1 <<code>>   
'|_ **expectedDateOfDelivery** 1..1 <<date>>        (ClinicalObservation)
'|_ **expectedNumberOfChildren** 1..1 <<integer>>   (ClinicalObservation)
'|_ **actualDateOfEndOfPregnancy** 0..1 <<date>>    (ClinicalObservation)
}

class "**expectedDateOfDelivery**\n(ClinicalObservation)" as edd {
|_ value 1..1 <<date>>
}


class "**expectedNumberOfChildren**\n(ClinicalObservation)" as enc {
|_ value 1..1 <<integer>>
}


class "**actualDateOfEndOfPregnancy**\n(ClinicalObservation)" as ade {
|_ value 1..1 <<date>>
}

' ── Detail observations: relationships + cardinalities ───────────────────────
' Multiplicities are taken from the logical model PregnancyStatusDataSet1.
'
' SOLID  = the PARENT knows its children: PregnancyStatus groups the member
'          observations (Observation.hasMember). The children do NOT point back,
'          so a member observation never changes when grouped here.
PSO "1" o-u- "1..1" edd
PSO "1" o-u- "1..1" enc
PSO "1" o-r- "0..1" ade

' DASHED = can be ADDED LATER, no redesign: when a Condition is introduced it is
'          the OBSERVATION that references the parent (e.g. Observation.focus).
'          The observation itself is unchanged.
edd "1..1" .u.> "0..1" PREG : focus
enc "1..1" .u.> "0..1" PREG : focus
PSO "0..1" .u.> "0..1" PREG : focus

' Option B: the Condition is summarized into the PregnancyStatus observation
'PREG "1" ..> "1" PSO : <<summarized as>>

note left of PREG
  **Full Scope** - we use the **Condition**
  (the pregnancy as a clinical episode),
  as a context and "parent" object.
end note

note left of PSO
  **Option 1** - only the PregnancyStatus Observation
  (IPS-compatible). No Condition exchanged. 
  When Pregnancy (Condition) exists, the PregnancyStatus 
  may have a reference (identifier) to the actual Pregnancy.
end note

legend bottom
  **Compatibility **
  
  It is possible to use **PregnancyStatus** (Observation) + member observations.  
  The **parent knows its children** (Observation.hasMember); the children do not
  point back. So a member observation (EDD, number of children, end date)
  **never changes intrinsically** when it is grouped under a PregnancyStatus.
  
  A **Pregnancy (Condition)** and its relationships can be **added later**.
  In that case it is the **observation that references the parent**
  (e.g. Observation.focus, or an extension). Adding the Condition therefore
  does **not** require redesigning the existing observations - the very same
  observation may simply *also* be referenced from a Condition.

  The Condition may also be used without the Observation Status - the options 
  are therefore mutually compatible.


endlegend

@enduml
